com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.framework.extensions

Interface ISCUIResourcePermission

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SCUIResourcePermission

    public interface ISCUIResourcePermission
    The implementation of this interface is used to define all the permission for a resource given by a ResourceId during the authorization. rasrinivasan

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean canExecute()
      Returns true if the user has permission to execute the resource given by ResourceId during authorization; otherwise false.
      boolean canRead()
      Returns true if the user has permission to read the resource given by ResourceId during authorization; otherwise false.
      boolean canWrite()
      Returns true if the user has permission to write the resource given by ResourceId during authorization; otherwise false.
